description: Manage orchestrator instance service with dnc.

commands.name: az dnc orchestrator-instance-service create
commands.syntax:
az dnc orchestrator-instance-service create --name
                                            --resource-group
                                            [--api-server-endpoint]
                                            [--cluster-root-ca]
                                            [--id]
                                            [--kind {Kubernetes}]
                                            [--location]
                                            [--no-wait {0, 1, f, false, n, no, t, true, y, yes}]
                                            [--orchestrator-app-id]
                                            [--orchestrator-tenant-id]
                                            [--priv-link-resource-id]
                                            [--tags]
                                            [--type {None, SystemAssigned}]

commands.name: az dnc orchestrator-instance-service delete
commands.syntax:
az dnc orchestrator-instance-service delete [--force-delete {0, 1, f, false, n, no, t, true, y, yes}]
                                            [--ids]
                                            [--name]
                                            [--no-wait {0, 1, f, false, n, no, t, true, y, yes}]
                                            [--resource-group]
                                            [--subscription]
                                            [--yes]

commands.name: az dnc orchestrator-instance-service show
commands.summary: Get details about the orchestrator instance.

commands.name: az dnc orchestrator-instance-service wait
commands.summary: Place the CLI in a waiting state until a condition is met.
